# -----------------MYSQL Connection with Django server---------------

# # -----------------HTTP METHODS----------------
#     1. creating/inserting data ---> Post 
#     2. retriving/getting data ---> GET 
#     3. updating/replacing data ---> put/patch 
#     4. deleting data ---> DELETE 

# # -------------status codes-----  
#  If work request is successful then we can give code ---> 2xx 
#  IF you are making request to one url but that url is moved to other address then we give status code -->301 
#  While making a request, if client/user made any mistakes ---> 4xx 
#  If errors in server like (logic,issue,db issue,server down) --> 5xx 

# #-----------HTTP CODES IMPORTANT TABLE-------------- 
# category   status code    name          menaing                  when to use (django/Api) 

# 2xx           200         ok             request sucess              GET Data , update success 
# 2xx           201         created        resourece created           post(create student,upload file) 
# 2xx           204         no content     delete sucessfully          delete operation 
# 3xx           301        moved permanent  url permantly changed      old url --> new url 
# 3xx           302        found            temporay redirect           login redirect 
# 4xx           400        bad request      invalid input from client  validating errors 
# 4xx           401       unauthorized      authentication required    token missing/invalid 
# 4xx           403       forbidden         no permission              authentication but blocked  
# 4xx           404       not found         resource not found         wrong ID/URL
# 4xx           405      method not aloowed   wrong http method        post instead of GET 
# 5xx           500     Internal server error  server crashed        unhandeled exception 
# 5xx           503       service unavailable   server down            maintainance/overload  


# # ----mysql connection with Django server ---------------- 

# # ORM-object relational mapping  

# # concept   ORM  

# # table     model 
# # row       object  
# # column    field  
# # query     orm methods   

